article.headline: Texas-Pan American 82, Houston Baptist 68
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas (AP) -- Paul Stoll scored a career-high 37 points to lead Texas-Pan American to an 82-68 victory over Houston Baptist Tuesday night. Stoll was perfect from the free-throw line, making all 16 attempts. He attempted nine 3-pointers, making seven of them. Those were his only field goal attempts. Stoll also had nine assists and seven rebounds for Texas-Pan American (12-10). Zach Trader had a double-double for the Broncs with 18 points and 12 rebounds. Nathan Hawkins added 10 points and five rebounds. The Broncs shot 52 percent from 3-point range -- compared to 22 percent for Houston Baptist -- and 81 percent from the free-throw line, making 21 of 23 attempts. Gordon Watt led Houston Baptist (7-15) with 17 points and nine rebounds. Baron Sauls scored 11.
